Spanish Stocks: Mapfre, Gas Natural, Repsol, Solaria Shares Move

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-03-15T17:09:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/spanish-stocks-mapfre-gas-natural-repsol-solaria-shares-move.html
  Spain ’s IBEX 35 index fell 86.2, or
0.8 percent, to 10,329.7 at the 5:30 p.m. close in Madrid. The
Madrid Stock Exchange General Index also dropped 0.8 percent
today.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Spanish market. Symbols are in parentheses after company names.    Mapfre SA (MAP)   sank 1.9 percent to 2.52 euros,
extending yesterday’s loss. Spain’s biggest insurer fell,
following insurers across  Europe  lower, after Japan’s biggest
earthquake on record triggered a seven-meter tsunami, killing at
least 2,000 people.  Nyesa Valores Corp. SA (NYE SM) slumped 3.2 percent to 1.22
euros, erasing yesterday’s gain. The Spanish real-estate
developer said it will hold a 1.85 million-euro ($2.57 million)
capital increase, according to a regulatory filing.    Repsol YPF SA (REP)   dropped for a fifth day, losing 2.1
percent to 22.49 euros, as energy producers retreated, following
the price of crude oil lower.  Iberdrola (IBE SM) fell 1.3 percent to 5.90 euros.  Gas
Natural SDG SA (GAS)   slid 2.1 percent to 12.14 euros and  Endesa SA (ELE)   slipped 1.4 percent to 20.88 euros.    Solaria Energia y Medio Ambiente SA (SLR)   soared 26
percent to 2.14 euros, the steepest gain since its initial
public offering. Manufacturers of solar power and wind energy
equipment climbed in Europe for a second day on speculation that
alternative-energy shares will benefit in the aftermath of
Japan’s nuclear accident.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in  Madrid  at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at   arummer@bloomberg.net  